                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=hendri.smit",
                        "name": "hendri.smit",
                        "displayName": "Hendri Smit",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Your regex pattern doesn't have any delimiters so it is invalid. That's why the exception is thrown.\r\nThe preg_match function will only return false if the pattern is incorrect. It returns 0 if no match was found.\r\n\r\nThis is not a bug. Read http:\/\/php.net\/manual\/en\/book.pcre.php for more info on regular expressions in PHP.\r\n",
